# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES — REQUIRED FOR LOCAL DEVELOPMENT AND PRODUCTION
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. SUPABASE (REQUIRED)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Get these from your Supabase project dashboard:
# https://supabase.com/dashboard/project/YOUR_PROJECT_ID/settings/api

# Your Supabase project URL (e.g. https://abcdefg.supabase.co)
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.supabase.co

# Your Supabase anonymous/public key (safe to expose in client code)
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 2. WEB PUSH NOTIFICATIONS (OPTIONAL BUT RECOMMENDED)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Generate VAPID keys using:
# npx web-push generate-vapid-keys
# 
# Then add VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY as a Supabase secret:
# supabase secrets set VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY="BF6w..."
# supabase secrets set VAPID_PRIVATE_KEY="a3s..."
# supabase secrets set VAPID_SUBJECT="mailto:you@example.com"

# VAPID public key (base64url encoded, 65 bytes uncompressed EC P-256 public key)
# This goes in the client app for push subscription
VITE_VAPID_PUBLIC_KEY=BF6w...

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 3. SUPABASE EDGE FUNCTIONS (SERVER-SIDE ONLY)
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# These are automatically injected by Supabase into Edge Functions
# You only need to set these manually if testing locally with Supabase CLI

# Service role key (NEVER expose this in client code)
# Used by Edge Functions to bypass RLS and send push notifications
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...

# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# QUICK START GUIDE
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# 1. Create a Supabase project at https://supabase.com/dashboard
# 2. Copy .env.example to .env
# 3. Fill in VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY from your dashboard
# 4. (Optional) Generate VAPID keys and add them to Supabase secrets
# 5. Run the SQL schema files in Supabase SQL Editor (see README.md)
# 6. Start the dev server: npm run dev
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
